1
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:07,319
Eighteen thousand.

2
00:01:08,319 --> 00:01:09,879
How? How is it eighteen thousand?

3
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:12,079
How many rooms would I have to sell?

4
00:01:19,799 --> 00:01:21,519
Party Secretary, Haoran, what a coincidence.

5
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:22,359
Just soaking up some sun.

6
00:01:22,959 --> 00:01:24,120
You enjoy it, I'll get going.

7
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,120
Coincidence, my foot.

8
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,959
I've been waiting here for half an hour.

9
00:01:29,439 --> 00:01:30,359
You got the document, right?

10
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:33,439
Meiduo said you took her Lingzhi and...

11
00:01:33,599 --> 00:01:34,879
I know, I know.

12
00:01:34,879 --> 00:01:37,560
Eighteen thousand, germplasm, support funds.

13
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:38,760
I've memorized it all.

14
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:40,560
Look here.

15
00:01:40,719 --> 00:01:41,599
It says right here,

16
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,879
"directly caused the loss of application materials,

17
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:46,480
core physical evidence."

18
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,799
I looked up these words.

19
00:01:48,079 --> 00:01:50,519
Meaning Meiduo's pinning the blame all on me.

20
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,719
You brought this on yourself.

21
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,680
Meiduo grew it for three years,

22
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:55,959
and you stewed it in one pot.

23
00:01:56,319 --> 00:01:57,079
And you feel wronged?

24
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,040
I don't feel wronged.

25
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:00,519
I just can't wrap my head around it.

26
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,040
The Lingzhi was growing out in the wild,

27
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,120
with no sign on it.

28
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,400
How was I supposed to know she grew it?

29
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,640
Zaxi, you really make me...

30
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,480
What am I supposed to say to you?

31
00:02:07,079 --> 00:02:08,919
Now's not the time to assign blame.

32
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:09,879
It's time to fix it.

33
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:10,759
Fix it?

34
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:11,840
How do I fix it?

35
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:17,800
I'll go up the mountain and find her another one.

36
00:02:17,879 --> 00:02:19,560
Go find one. Think you can?

37
00:02:20,919 --> 00:02:22,039
Then what should I do?

38
00:02:24,199 --> 00:02:26,039
First, go to Meiduo's house and apologize in person.

39
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,439
Fine, I'll go apologize.

40
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,120
Wait.

41
00:02:31,879 --> 00:02:33,159
Be sincere about it.

42
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:34,319
Don't be all grins and giggles.

43
00:02:34,879 --> 00:02:36,000
No smart mouth, speak properly.

44
00:02:36,439 --> 00:02:37,240
Admit your mistake to her face.

45
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,400
Got it, got it.

46
00:02:43,319 --> 00:02:44,840
That kid, ever since he was little,

47
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:47,280
his mouth's always been his best weapon.

48
00:02:47,639 --> 00:02:48,039
Party Secretary,

49
00:02:48,719 --> 00:02:50,599
do you think Meiduo will forgive him?

50
00:02:51,479 --> 00:02:52,639
I know that girl.

51
00:02:53,199 --> 00:02:53,759
Stubborn.

52
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,520
But she's reasonable.

53
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,560
As long as Zaxi is sincere,

54
00:02:58,439 --> 00:02:59,080
it should work out.

55
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,599
And what if he isn't sincere?

56
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,159
Then you can scrape together that eighteen thousand.

57
00:03:06,919 --> 00:03:07,400
Hey!

58
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,680
I've still got village business to attend to.

59
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:11,680
I gotta go.

60
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,120
That little rascal, slow down!

61
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:22,719
Zaxi, you're here.

62
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,479
I came to see Meiduo.

63
00:03:26,879 --> 00:03:28,759
You used to come to our house all the time.

64
00:03:29,159 --> 00:03:31,159
You and Meiduo would lie on the ground watching ants.

65
00:03:31,919 --> 00:03:33,479
Auntie, that was all when we were kids.

66
00:03:34,639 --> 00:03:36,199
You picked her Lingzhi back then,

67
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:37,879
and now you've stewed her Lingzhi.

68
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:38,599
Look at you.

69
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,960
Why do you keep doing this?

70
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,560
Auntie, I came today to apologize.

71
00:03:43,439 --> 00:03:44,879
She's inside, go on in.

72
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:48,319
Auntie.

73
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,199
These eggs are from our old hen.

74
00:03:50,919 --> 00:03:51,360
Okay.

75
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,199
I'll cook them for Duoji tonight.

76
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:53,960
Good.

77
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,919
Meiduo, can I come in?

78
00:04:04,919 --> 00:04:05,960
You're already in.

79
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,840
I was just worried you'd be upset.

80
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:19,959
What's going on here?

81
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:22,759
Dad's raising it.

82
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,000
He said the barn's too cold,

83
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:25,759
so he let it come in to warm up.

84
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,079
I get the warming up part.

85
00:04:27,079 --> 00:04:29,040
I meant, what's this mess?

86
00:04:33,879 --> 00:04:34,399
It pooped.

87
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,439
I know it pooped.

88
00:04:37,439 --> 00:04:39,399
The point is, it can't poop indoors!

89
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,040
You're asking me?

90
00:04:41,199 --> 00:04:42,079
Who am I supposed to ask?

91
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,040
How could you just poop inside?

92
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,279
What did you just lick?

93
00:04:47,279 --> 00:04:48,319
And now you're licking my hand!

94
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,720
It likes you.

95
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:53,600
Oh, you like me?

96
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,120
I like you too.

97
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:56,439
You need to eat more,

98
00:04:56,439 --> 00:04:57,399
so you grow up big and strong.

99
00:04:58,439 --> 00:04:58,959
Hey, what are you doing?

100
00:04:58,959 --> 00:05:00,439
You're trying to eat my hand too!

101
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:04,399
You smiled.

102
00:05:06,839 --> 00:05:07,279
No, I didn't.

103
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,800
I just saw it. You smiled.

104
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:10,720
You saw wrong.

105
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:11,639
I didn't see wrong.

106
00:05:11,639 --> 00:05:12,519
You totally smiled, I mean it.

107
00:05:16,839 --> 00:05:19,079
Since you let me see Meiduo smile,

108
00:05:19,519 --> 00:05:20,920
I'll forgive you for that mess.

109
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:22,319
What a smart mouth you've got.

110
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:24,199
Okay, I'll stop.

111
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,079
I came to apologize.

112
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,240
Apologize?

113
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:35,120
About that Lingzhi plant.

114
00:05:35,519 --> 00:05:36,199
I'm sorry.

115
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,800
I didn't know you'd planted it.

116
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:41,519
Do you know what that Lingzhi

117
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:42,879
meant to me?

118
00:05:44,079 --> 00:05:44,680
Germplasm.

119
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:45,920
With it,

120
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:48,439
the village could build an under-forest planting base.

121
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,759
In three years,

122
00:05:50,279 --> 00:05:52,199
each household could earn 20 or 30 thousand more.

123
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:53,279
20 or 30 thousand?

124
00:05:53,399 --> 00:05:53,920
Yes.

125
00:05:54,439 --> 00:05:55,480
Per household.

126
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:58,000
Everyone in the village would benefit.

127
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,839
I came back with this project.

128
00:06:03,639 --> 00:06:05,920
Government funding and the tech team are all set.

129
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,040
We just needed that parent plant.

130
00:06:07,319 --> 00:06:08,399
Now that it's gone,

131
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,959
the project has to be delayed.

132
00:06:10,639 --> 00:06:13,199
Each year delayed means a year of lost income.

133
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,600
I had no idea.

134
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,600
Of course you didn't.

135
00:06:17,279 --> 00:06:19,360
You didn't just pick my Lingzhi,

136
00:06:19,639 --> 00:06:21,160
but the whole village's income.

137
00:06:24,319 --> 00:06:25,079
I'm sorry.

138
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,879
So how do I fix it?

139
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:44,040
Well, there's still a way.

140
00:06:45,319 --> 00:06:46,480
Just tell me what to do.

141
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,399
I planted more than just one back then.

142
00:06:50,759 --> 00:06:52,560
There should be other surviving

143
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,600
germplasm on the mountain.

144
00:06:54,199 --> 00:06:55,959
It just takes luck and time to search.

145
00:06:56,319 --> 00:06:57,199
That's great!

146
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,040
I'll help you look.

147
00:06:58,480 --> 00:07:00,319
I have to go with or without your help.

148
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,720
You'll be the guide.

149
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,439
We'll go up the mountain together.

150
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,240
I'll be the guide.

151
00:07:06,879 --> 00:07:08,120
And carry the equipment.

152
00:07:08,759 --> 00:07:09,160
I'll carry it.

153
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:11,720
Also,

154
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:13,399
the air at my place isn't up to standard.

155
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,319
I need a place to store my things.

156
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,439
My guesthouse!

157
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,519
It's clean, and Jimei cooks too.

158
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:20,680
You sure?

159
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:21,759
To redeem myself.

160
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:22,920
For the whole village.

161
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,120
Fine.

162
00:07:26,319 --> 00:07:26,920
It's a deal.

163
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:28,839
Thank you, Dr. Meiduo.

164
00:07:31,759 --> 00:07:33,160
Don't celebrate too soon.

165
00:07:33,759 --> 00:07:34,879
If anything else goes wrong,

166
00:07:34,879 --> 00:07:36,160
that 18,000 must be paid in full.

167
00:07:36,439 --> 00:07:38,319
And you'll be on the hook for the village's losses too.

168
00:07:39,399 --> 00:07:39,879
Got it.

169
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,199
Alright.

170
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,519
It's getting late.

171
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:44,720
You should head home.

172
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,399
Come pick me up tomorrow.

173
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,279
Okay.

174
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:49,959
I'm leaving then.

175
00:07:50,319 --> 00:07:50,959
Goodbye.

176
00:07:59,839 --> 00:08:01,439
Do you think he's a bit silly?

177
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,519
I think he's a bit silly too.

178
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:18,040
Meiduo.

179
00:08:18,439 --> 00:08:19,079
Try some.

180
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:20,959
Does it still taste the same?

181
00:08:22,279 --> 00:08:23,199
Hasn't changed a bit.

182
00:08:23,199 --> 00:08:24,360
Thank you, Uncle Jimei.

183
00:08:24,639 --> 00:08:25,040
Good.

184
00:08:25,319 --> 00:08:26,800
Drink up and eat plenty.

185
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:29,839
Meiduo.

186
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,240
About that 18,000 thing,

187
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,840
you're letting him off that easy?

188
00:08:38,639 --> 00:08:39,559
I was just teasing him.

189
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:41,440
Who told him to go picking them?

190
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,279
He needed a little lesson.

191
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:43,840
By the way,

192
00:08:44,519 --> 00:08:45,919
this stays between us, okay?

193
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,399
You can count on me.

194
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:55,039
Uncle Liu.

195
00:08:55,039 --> 00:08:55,840
Jimei.

196
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,559
Zaxi, come unload the truck!

197
00:08:58,879 --> 00:08:59,360
Zaxi.

198
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,600
Uncle Liu, you're early today.

199
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:05,919
You call this early?

200
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,519
Didn't I tell you before?

201
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:10,399
Cucumbers picked before sunrise

202
00:09:10,519 --> 00:09:11,360
are the crispiest.

203
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,279
Qianqian, come try one.

204
00:09:13,279 --> 00:09:13,840
Thank you.

205
00:09:14,399 --> 00:09:15,200
Our guest from afar,

206
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:15,679
you try one too.

207
00:09:17,759 --> 00:09:19,159
Uncle Liu,

208
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:21,080
I've been standing here for a while,

209
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,399
and you still don't recognize me?

210
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:24,159
You are...

211
00:09:25,159 --> 00:09:26,519
Meiduo!

212
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:29,279
I didn't recognize you at all!

213
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:30,440
You've grown so much!

214
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:32,679
It's been so long,

215
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:34,240
and you're still a master at growing veggies.

216
00:09:34,799 --> 00:09:37,039
This is the Jinyan No. 4 Improved Version, right?

217
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,600
With sheep manure as base fertilizer.

218
00:09:40,039 --> 00:09:40,799
This girl's amazing!

219
00:09:40,799 --> 00:09:41,639
How did you know?

220
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,879
You taught me how to grow veggies when I was little.

221
00:09:43,879 --> 00:09:45,000
You always said I was the quickest learner.

222
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:45,879
Forgot already?

223
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,480
No, I could never forget that.

224
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,559
When this girl was little,

225
00:09:50,559 --> 00:09:51,519
in my greenhouse,

226
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:52,960
she'd follow me around,

227
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,200
asking questions nonstop.

228
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,320
I'll never forget that.

229
00:09:56,759 --> 00:09:57,600
I heard

230
00:09:57,799 --> 00:09:59,120
you went and studied agriculture, right?

231
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:01,240
Even got a PhD. Impressive!

232
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,440
That's right, Uncle Liu.

233
00:10:03,639 --> 00:10:05,320
She's the pride of our village.

234
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,399
Look, she flew out and flew right back,

235
00:10:07,559 --> 00:10:09,080
and she can even smell the sheep manure.

236
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:10,600
That's exactly what I studied.

237
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,360
Uncle Liu,

238
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,919
I'm back to do under-forest planting,

239
00:10:14,919 --> 00:10:17,279
and I'll need to borrow sheep manure for the test fields.

240
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:19,080
Borrow? Sheep manure?

241
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:19,960
Sure!

242
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:20,720
I might not have much else,

243
00:10:20,919 --> 00:10:22,879
but sheep manure? As much as you want.

244
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:23,320
Great.

245
00:10:23,679 --> 00:10:24,399
Then it's a deal.

246
00:10:24,399 --> 00:10:25,039
It's a deal.

247
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,240
I told you all along,

248
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,639
there's real science in this soil.

249
00:10:27,759 --> 00:10:28,559
None of you believed me.

250
00:10:28,639 --> 00:10:29,200
Now look,

251
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:29,919
the expert's here.

252
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:31,840
You'll have to teach us a thing or two.

253
00:10:32,559 --> 00:10:33,320
Meiduo,

254
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,320
you came back this time

255
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,519
specifically to do under-forest planting?

256
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:39,200
I brought back the Lingzhi No. 1 project.

257
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:41,080
No cutting trees, no destroying forests.

258
00:10:41,399 --> 00:10:42,919
Just growing edible fungi under the trees.

259
00:10:42,919 --> 00:10:44,240
So everyone can prosper.

260
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:44,799
That's great!

261
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,039
Uncle Liu supports you.

262
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:47,480
From now on, my greenhouse

263
00:10:47,679 --> 00:10:48,919
will be your supply base.

264
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:49,919
You need people, you got 'em.

265
00:10:50,919 --> 00:10:51,519
You need manure, you got it.

266
00:10:53,799 --> 00:10:55,159
But if we really don't have to cut trees

267
00:10:55,159 --> 00:10:56,120
and still make money,

268
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:58,120
then losing my 18,000 wasn't for nothing.

269
00:10:59,120 --> 00:10:59,799
What did you say?

270
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:00,519
I'm saying,

271
00:11:01,039 --> 00:11:03,080
look, Uncle Liu's even donating fertilizer.

272
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:05,480
Can my debt be reduced a little?

273
00:11:05,559 --> 00:11:06,360
In your dreams.

274
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,440
Up the mountain at 8:30.

275
00:11:08,559 --> 00:11:11,080
Every minute late adds a 10 yuan late fee.

276
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:12,600
I'm heading out.

277
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,720
Uncle Jimei, I'm leaving first.

278
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:15,960
Okay, goodbye.

279
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:16,759
Hey, kiddo,

280
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:18,039
come check out my greenhouse sometime.

281
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:18,600
Sure.

282
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,600
Remember to bring the drone!

283
